{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865397861,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d36f5c001fXXbEwl4cH7BQh","messageID":"msg_d79d3646d0015Y9xgKhZm1fyAh","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_c85d43978b4341d994d99b6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","pattern":"**/AR-020*.md"},"output":"No files found","metadata":{"count":0,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","time":{"start":1775865397834,"end":1775865397860}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865397883,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d37b30001rE1He9ugrIEpU9","messageID":"msg_d79d3646d0015Y9xgKhZm1fyAh","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2592a2b4de13471f9460c12a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","limit":100,"offset":1},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: The PicoD File Management API provides:\n12: \n13: 1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n14: 2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n15: 3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n16: 4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n17: 5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n18: \n19: This implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: - `pkg/picod/filesystem.go` - File operations interface and implementation\n28: - `pkg/picod/fileinfo.go` - File metadata and information structures\n29: - `pkg/picod/quota.go` - Disk quota management and enforcement\n30: - `pkg/picod/path.go` - Path validation and normalization utilities\n31: - `pkg/picod/filesystem_test.go` - File operation unit tests\n32: - `pkg/picod/quota_test.go` - Quota management tests\n33: - `pkg/picod/path_test.go` - Path validation tests\n34: - `pkg/picod/integration_test.go` - Integration tests (extended)\n35: \n36: ### Out of Scope\n37: \n38: - Network filesystem support (NFS, SMB, etc.)\n39: - File watching/notification systems\n40: - Advanced permissions (ACLs, extended attributes)\n41: - File encryption/decryption\n42: - Distributed file locking\n43: - Backup and snapshot functionality\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Package | Purpose |\n52: |---------|---------|\n53: | `os` | File operations and metadata |\n54: | `io` | Stream operations |\n55: | `io/fs` | Filesystem interfaces |\n56: | `path/filepath` | Path manipulation |\n57: | `context` | Operation cancellation and timeouts |\n58: | `syscall` | Low-level filesystem operations |\n59: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n60: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Existing PicoD types and limits |\n61: \n62: ### Affected Components\n63: \n64: 1. **Code Interpreter**: Will use file API for reading/writing code files and outputs\n65: 2. **Agent Runtime**: Will use file API for accessing configuration and state files\n66: 3. **Workload Manager**: Will use file API for managing job artifacts\n67: 4. **Sandbox Manager**: Will configure filesystem quotas and permissions\n68: 5. **Security Module**: Will validate file operation permissions\n69: \n70: ### Backward Compatibility\n71: \n72: - This is a new API surface within the existing PicoD module\n73: - No breaking changes to existing AR-015 command execution APIs\n74: - Extends PicoD struct with additional methods\n75: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n76: \n77: ### Risk Assessment\n78: \n79: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n80: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n81: | Path traversal attack | Medium | Critical | Strict path validation, chroot-style isolation |\n82: | Disk space exhaustion | High | High | Enforce quotas, validate write sizes |\n83: | Symlink attacks | Medium | High | Resolve and validate symlink targets |\n84: | Race conditions | Medium | Medium | Atomic operations where possible, proper locking |\n85: | Information disclosure | Low | High | Validate read operations, enforce permissions |\n86: | Directory depth attacks | Low | Medium | Enforce maximum directory depth limits |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Alternatives Considered\n91: \n92: ### Alternative 1: Use os.* Directly\n93: \n94: **Approach**: Expose standard library `os` package functions directly\n95: \n96: **Pros**:\n97: - Minimal implementation effort\n98: - No additional abstraction layer\n99: - Full control for callers\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 502. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API (AR-016)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the file management API for the PicoD module in `pkg/picod`, providing secure file operations within sandboxed environments including read, write, list, and delete capabilities with proper security validations and resource limits.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides:\n\n1. **Secure File Operations**: Read, write, list, and delete files within controlled sandbox directories\n2. **Path Validation**: Ensure all file operations stay within allowed workspace boundaries\n3. **Resource Limits**: Enforce file size limits, directory depth limits, and quota management\n4. **Atomic Operations**: Support for atomic write operations to prevent partial writes\n5. **Metadata Access**: Retrieve file metadata (size, modification time, permissions)\n\nThis implementation builds upon the command execution infrastructure from AR-015 and provides the file management layer needed for code interpreters and agent runtimes to interact with the filesystem safely.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775865397844,"end":1775865397880}}}}
