{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865404383,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d3973d001ENIW0L84Kopzph","messageID":"msg_d79d382b0001rIXLyz2mW5RJlu","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_475d5b2fbe2e42cdbb99d388","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: Specs:\n9: --- cli-toolkit/design.md ---\n10: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n11: \n12: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n13: \n14: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n15: \n16: | Path | Role |\n17: |------|------|\n18: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n19: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n20: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n21: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n22: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n23: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n24: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n25: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n26: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n27: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n28: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n29: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n30: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n31: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n32: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n33: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n34: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n35: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n36: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n37: \n38: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n39: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n40: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n41: \n42: ## Console script entry point\n43: \n44: ```toml\n45: [project.scripts]\n46: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n47: ```\n48: \n49: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n50: \n51: ## Typer — root callback\n52: \n53: ```python\n54: def main(\n55:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n56:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n57:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n58:     ),\n59:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n60: ) -> None:\n61:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Typer — `pack`\n65: \n66: ```python\n67: def pack(\n68:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n69:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n70:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n71:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n72:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n73:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n74:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n75:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n76:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n77: ) -> None:\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ## Typer — `build`\n81: \n82: ```python\n83: def build(\n84:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n85:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n86:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n87:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n88:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n89: ) -> None:\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## Typer — `publish`\n93: \n94: ```python\n95: def publish(\n96:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n97:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n98:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n99:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n100:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n101:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n102:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n103:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n104:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n105:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n106:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n107:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n108:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n109: ) -> None:\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Typer — `invoke`\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: def invoke(\n116:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n117:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n118:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n119:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n120:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n121: ) -> None:\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ## Typer — `status`\n125: \n126: ```python\n127: def status(\n128:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n129:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n130:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n131: ) -> None:\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n138: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ## Runtime classes\n142: \n143: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n144: \n145: ```python\n146: class PackRuntime:\n147:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n148:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n149:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n150:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n151:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n152:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n153:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n154:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n155:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n156:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n157:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n158:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n159:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n160:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n161:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n162:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n163:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n167: \n168: ```python\n169: class BuildRuntime:\n170:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n171:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n172:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n173:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n174:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n175:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n180: \n181: ```python\n182: class PublishRuntime:\n183:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n184:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n185:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n186:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n187:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n188:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n189:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n190:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n194: \n195: ```python\n196: class InvokeRuntime:\n197:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n198:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n199:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n200:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n201:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n205: \n206: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n207: \n208: ```python\n209: class StatusRuntime:\n210:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n211:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n212:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n213:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n217: \n218: ```python\n219: class DockerService:\n220:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n221:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n222:     def build_image(\n223:         self,\n224:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n225:         context_path: Path,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n228:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n229:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n230:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n232:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n233:     def push_image(\n234:         self,\n235:         image_name: str,\n236:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n237:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n238:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n239:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n240:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n241:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n242:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n243: ```\n244: \n245: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n246: \n247: ```python\n248: class MetadataService:\n249:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n250:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n251:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n252:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n253:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n254:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n255:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n259: \n260: ```python\n261: class KubernetesProvider:\n262:     def __init__(\n263:         self,\n264:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n265:         verbose: bool = False,\n266:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n267:     ) -> None: ...\n268:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n269:     def deploy_agent(\n270:         self,\n271:         agent_name: str,\n272:         image_url: str,\n273:         port: int,\n274:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n275:         replicas: int = 1,\n276:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n277:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n278:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n279:     def _create_deployment(\n280:         self,\n281:         name: str,\n282:         image_url: str,\n283:         port: int,\n284:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n285:         replicas: int,\n286:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n287:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n288:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n289:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n290:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n291:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n292:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n296: \n297: ```python\n298: class AgentCubeProvider:\n299:     def __init__(\n300:         self,\n301:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n302:         verbose: bool = False,\n303:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n304:     ) -> None: ...\n305:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n306:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n307:         self,\n308:         agent_name: str,\n309:         image_url: str,\n310:         port: int,\n311:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n312:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n313:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n314:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n315:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n316:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n317:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n318:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n319:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n320: ```\n321: \n322: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n323: \n324: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n325: \n326: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n327: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n328: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n329: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n330: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n331: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n332: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n333: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n334: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n335: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n336: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n337: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n338: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n339: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n340: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n341: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n342: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n343: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n344: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n345: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n346: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n347: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n348: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n349: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n350: \n351: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n352: \n353: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n354: \n355: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n356: \n357: | Field | Type | Default |\n358: |-------|------|---------|\n359: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n360: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n361: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n362: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n363: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n364: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n365: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n366: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n367: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n368: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n369: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n370: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n371: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n372: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n373: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n374: \n375: ```python\n376: @classmethod\n377: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n378: ```\n379: \n380: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n381: \n382: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n383: \n384: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n385: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n386: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n387: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n388: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n389: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n390: - `packaging>=23.0`\n391: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n392: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n393: \n394: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n395: \n396: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n397: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n398: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n399: \n400: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n401: \n402: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n403: \n404: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n405: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n406: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n407: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n408: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n409:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n410: \n411: \n412: --- cli-toolkit/spec.md ---\n413: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n414: \n415: ## Purpose\n416: \n417: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n418: \n419: ## Requirements\n420: \n421: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n422: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Version display\n425: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n426: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n427: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n430: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n431: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n432: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n433: \n434: ### Requirement: `pack` command\n435: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n438: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n439: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n440: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Successful pack\n443: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n444: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n445: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n448: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n449: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n450: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: `build` command\n453: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n454: \n455: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n456: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n457: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n458: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n459: \n460: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n461: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n462: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n463: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n464: \n465: #### Scenario: Version increment on build\n466: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n467: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n468: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n469: \n470: ### Requirement: `publish` command\n471: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n474: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n475: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n478: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n479: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n480: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n481: \n482: #### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n483: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n484: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n485: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n486: \n487: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n488: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n489: \n490: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n491: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n492: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n493: \n494: #### Scenario: Invalid payload\n495: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n496: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n497: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n498: \n499: #### Scenario: Invalid header format\n500: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n501: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n502: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n503: \n504: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n505: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n506: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n507: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: `status` command\n510: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n511: \n512: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n513: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n514: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: Not published\n517: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n518: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n519: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n520: \n521: ### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n522: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Missing workspace\n525: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n526: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n527: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n530: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n531: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n532: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n533: \n534: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n535: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: Save location\n538: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n539: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n540: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n541: \n542: #### Scenario: Schema validation\n543: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n544: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n545: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n546: \n547: ### Requirement: Docker integration\n548: The system SHALL use the Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) to build images, push to a registry when configured, and optionally remove images.\n549: \n550: #### Scenario: Build image\n551: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n552: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n553: - **THEN** it SHALL tag `{image_name}:{tag}`, pass optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, and return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n554: \n555: #### Scenario: Push image\n556: - **GIVEN** a local image name and optional `registry_url` / credentials\n557: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image` runs\n558: - **THEN** it SHALL login if username and password are provided, retag when needed, stream push logs, and return `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n559: \n560: #### Scenario: Remove image\n561: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n562: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n563: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`; on failure it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n564: \n565: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — standard provider\n566: The system SHALL create or patch `Deployment` and `NodePort` `Service`, wait for rollout, report pod status, and support deletion.\n567: \n568: #### Scenario: Deploy agent\n569: - **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` is called\n570: - **WHEN** resources are applied\n571: - **THEN** the result SHALL include `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}`\n572: \n573: #### Scenario: Wait for ready\n574: - **GIVEN** a deployment name\n575: - **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready` exceeds `timeout` seconds (default `120`)\n576: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `TimeoutError`\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Delete agent\n579: - **GIVEN** `delete_agent` is called\n580: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n581: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` ignoring 404 on individual deletes\n582: \n583: ### Requirement: Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n584: The system SHALL create or patch an `AgentRuntime` custom object in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, plural `agentruntimes`.\n585: \n586: #### Scenario: Deploy CR\n587: - **GIVEN** required readiness probe fields exist in metadata\n588: - **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` runs\n589: - **THEN** it SHALL embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from parameters or environment when missing in `env_vars`, set `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`, and reference `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n590: \n591: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n592: The system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for `provider=agentcube` publish/status flows and `KubernetesProvider` for `provider=k8s`.\n593: \n594: #### Scenario: Status for AgentRuntime\n595: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists\n596: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n597: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (`status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n598: \n599: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n600: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions: print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red; if `verbose`, print traceback; raise `typer.Exit(1)`.\n601: \n602: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n603: - **GIVEN** a subcommand’s local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n604: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n605: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand’s `verbose` flag\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: **Note:** The implementation uses `agent_metadata.yaml` as the canonical metadata filename (with `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml` fallbacks for load). Documentation that refers to `agentcube.yaml` SHALL be treated as naming drift unless a separate file is introduced in code.\n610: \n611: \n612: --- deployment/client-go.md ---\n613: # client-go library\n614: \n615: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n616: \n617: ## Clientset\n618: \n619: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n620: \n621: ```go\n622: type Interface interface {\n623: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n624: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n625: }\n626: ```\n627: \n628: ### `Clientset` struct\n629: \n630: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n631: \n632: **Constructors**\n633: \n634: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n635: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n636: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n637: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n638: \n639: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n640: \n641: ---\n642: \n643: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n644: \n645: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n646: \n647: ```go\n648: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n649: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n650: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n651: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n652: }\n653: ```\n654: \n655: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n656: \n657: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n658: \n659: ```go\n660: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n661: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n662: }\n663: \n664: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n665: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n666: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n667: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n668: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n669: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n670: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n671: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n672: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n673: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n674: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n675: }\n676: ```\n677: \n678: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n679: \n680: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n681: \n682: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n683: \n684: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n685: \n686: ```go\n687: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n688: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n689: ```\n690: \n691: (Empty — reserved for custom methods.)\n692: \n693: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n694: \n695: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` — test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n696: \n697: ---\n698: \n699: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n700: \n701: | File | Role |\n702: |------|------|\n703: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n704: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n705: \n706: ---\n707: \n708: ## Informer factory\n709: \n710: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n711: \n712: ```go\n713: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n714: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n715: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n716: \tShutdown()\n717: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n718: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n719: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n720: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n721: }\n722: ```\n723: \n724: **Constructors / options**\n725: \n726: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n727: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n728: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n729: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n730: \n731: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n732: \n733: ```go\n734: type Interface interface {\n735: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n736: }\n737: ```\n738: \n739: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n740: \n741: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n742: \n743: ```go\n744: type Interface interface {\n745: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n746: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n751: \n752: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n753: \n754: ```go\n755: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n756: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n757: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n758: }\n759: ```\n760: \n761: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n762: \n763: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n764: \n765: `ForResource` switches on:\n766: \n767: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` → `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n768: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` → `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n769: \n770: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n771: \n772: ```go\n773: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n774: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n775: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n776: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n777: }\n778: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n784: \n785: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n789: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n790: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n791: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n792: }\n793: \n794: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n795: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n796: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n797: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n798: }\n799: ```\n800: \n801: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n802: \n803: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n804: \n805: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n806: \n807: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n808: \n809: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n810: \n811: ---\n812: \n813: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n814: \n815: | File | Role |\n816: |------|------|\n817: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` — in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n818: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n819: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n820: \n821: ---\n822: \n823: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n824: \n825: | Path | Role |\n826: |------|------|\n827: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n828: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n829: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n830: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n831: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n832: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n833: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n834: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n835: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n836: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n837: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n838: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n839: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n840: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n841: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n842: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n843: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n844: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n845: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n846: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n847: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n848: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n849: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n850: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n851: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n852: \n853: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n854: \n855: \n856: --- python-sdk/design.md ---\n857: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n858: \n859: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n860: \n861: ## Package layout\n862: \n863: | Path | Role |\n864: |------|------|\n865: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n866: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n867: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n868: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n869: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n870: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n871: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n872: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n873: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n874: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n875: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n876: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n877: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n878: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n879: \n880: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n881: \n882: ```python\n883: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n884: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n885: \n886: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n887: ```\n888: \n889: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n890: \n891: ```python\n892: __all__ = [\n893:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n894:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n895:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n896: ]\n897: ```\n898: \n899: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n900: \n901: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n902: \n903: | Component | Resolved settings |\n904: |-----------|-------------------|\n905: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n906: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n907: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n908: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n909: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n910: \n911: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n912: \n913: ```python\n914: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n915:     def __init__(\n916:         self,\n917:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n918:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n919:         ttl: int = 3600,\n920:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n921:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n922:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n923:         verbose: bool = False,\n924:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n925:     ): ...\n926: \n927:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n928: \n929:     def __enter__(self): ...\n930:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n931: \n932:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n933: \n934:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n935:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n936:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n937:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n938:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n939:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n940: ```\n941: \n942: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n943: \n944: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n945: \n946: ```python\n947: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n948:     def __init__(\n949:         self,\n950:         agent_name: str,\n951:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n952:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n953:         verbose: bool = False,\n954:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n955:         timeout: int = 120,\n956:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n957:     ): ...\n958: \n959:     def __enter__(self): ...\n960:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n961: \n962:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n963: \n964:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n965: ```\n966: \n967: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n968: \n969: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n970: \n971: ```python\n972: class ControlPlaneClient:\n973:     def __init__(\n974:         self,\n975:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n976:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n977:         timeout: int = 120,\n978:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n979:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n980:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n981:     ): ...\n982: \n983:     def create_session(\n984:         self,\n985:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n986:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n987:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n988:         ttl: int = 3600,\n989:     ) -> str: ...\n990: \n991:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n992: \n993:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n994: ```\n995: \n996: ### Control plane — HTTP\n997: \n998: | Method | Path | Notes |\n999: |--------|------|-------|\n1000: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n1001: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n1002: \n1003: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n1004: \n1005: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n1006: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n1007: \n1008: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n1009: \n1010: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n1011: \n1012: ```python\n1013: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n1014:     def __init__(\n1015:         self,\n1016:         session_id: str,\n1017:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1018:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n1019:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n1020:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1021:         timeout: int = 120,\n1022:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1023:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n1024:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1025:     ): ...\n1026: \n1027:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n1028: \n1029:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1030:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n1031:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1032:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n1033:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n1034:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n1035:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1036: ```\n1037: \n1038: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n1039: \n1040: If `base_url` is not provided:\n1041: \n1042: ```text\n1043: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n1044: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1045: ```\n1046: \n1047: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n1048: \n1049: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n1050: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n1051: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n1052: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n1053: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n1054: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n1055: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n1056: \n1057: **Headers:**\n1058: \n1059: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n1060: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n1061: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n1062: \n1063: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n1064: \n1065: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n1066: \n1067: ```python\n1068: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n1069:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n1070: \n1071:     def __init__(\n1072:         self,\n1073:         router_url: str,\n1074:         namespace: str,\n1075:         agent_name: str,\n1076:         timeout: int = 120,\n1077:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n1078:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n1079:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1080:     ): ...\n1081: \n1082:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n1083: \n1084:     def invoke(\n1085:         self,\n1086:         session_id: str,\n1087:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n1088:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n1089:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n1090: \n1091:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n1092: ```\n1093: \n1094: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n1095: \n1096: ```text\n1097: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n1098: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n1099: ```\n1100: \n1101: ### Data plane — HTTP\n1102: \n1103: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n1104: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n1105: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n1106: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n1107: \n1108: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n1109: \n1110: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n1111: \n1112: ```python\n1113: def create_session(\n1114:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n1115:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n1116: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n1117: ```\n1118: \n1119: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n1120: \n1121: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n1122: \n1123: ```python\n1124: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n1125: ```\n1126: \n1127: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n1128: \n1129: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n1130: \n1131: ```python\n1132: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n1133: ```\n1134: \n1135: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n1136: \n1137: ```python\n1138: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n1139:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n1140:     pass\n1141: \n1142: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1142. Use offset=1143 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\nSpecs:\n--- cli-toolkit/design.md ---\n# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775865404363,"end":1775865404379}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865404392,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d38c0a001NjjQIqRrP61J4U","messageID":"msg_d79d382b0001rIXLyz2mW5RJlu","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9d3e720d9eff4469b824baf9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI Pack Command\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the `pack` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `pack` command validates and prepares agent workspaces, merges CLI overrides into metadata, generates Dockerfiles, and reports paths. This is the first command in the Python CLI toolkit that provides developer-friendly tooling for packaging AI agents for deployment on AgentCube.\n6: \n7: The goal is to:\n8: \n9: 1. **Provide workspace validation** - Ensure agent workspaces have the required structure and files for the target language (Python/Java)\n10: 2. **Enable metadata management** - Load, merge, and persist agent configuration as YAML\n11: 3. **Generate deployment artifacts** - Create Dockerfiles tailored to the agent's language and dependencies\n12: 4. **Support development workflows** - Enable developers to package agents with CLI overrides before building and publishing\n13: \n14: This implementation builds upon the Python SDK design (`python-sdk/design.md`) and CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`).\n15: \n16: ## Scope\n17: \n18: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n19: **Language:** Python  \n20: **Size:** M\n21: \n22: This AR covers:\n23: \n24: - **In scope:**\n25:   - `agentcube` Python package structure under `cmd/cli/`\n26:   - `PackRuntime` class implementation\n27:   - `pack` Typer command with all specified options\n28:   - Metadata validation and merging logic\n29:   - Dockerfile generation for Python and Java agents\n30:   - Workspace structure validation\n31:   - Dependency processing (requirements.txt for Python, pom.xml for Java)\n32:   - Error handling with verbose traceback support\n33:   - Unit tests for pack logic\n34:   - Documentation and usage examples\n35: \n36: - **Out of scope:**\n37:   - `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status` commands (future ARs)\n38:   - Docker SDK integration for actual image building\n39:   - Kubernetes client integration for deployment\n40:   - Cloud provider integrations\n41:   - AgentRuntime CR creation\n42: \n43: ## Current State Analysis\n44: \n45: ### Existing Python SDK\n46: \n47: Per `python-sdk/design.md`, the Python SDK provides:\n48: - `AgentRuntimeClient` for invoking deployed agents\n49: - `CodeInterpreterClient` for code execution sessions\n50: - Control plane and data plane HTTP clients\n51: - Exception hierarchy and utilities\n52: \n53: ### CLI Toolkit Specification\n54: \n55: Per `cli-toolkit/spec.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`:\n56: - CLI entry point: `kubectl-agentcube` via Typer\n57: - Package layout: `agentcube/` with `cli/`, `runtime/`, `services/`, `models/` subpackages\n58: - `PackRuntime` class with 17 methods specified\n59: - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 22 fields\n60: - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option parsing\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No Python CLI package** - The `cmd/cli/` directory does not exist\n65: 2. **No PackRuntime implementation** - Only the interface is specified in design docs\n66: 3. **No metadata service** - No implementation for loading/saving `agent_metadata.yaml`\n67: 4. **No Dockerfile generation** - No templates or generation logic exists\n68: 5. **No workspace validation** - No validation logic for Python/Java workspaces\n69: \n70: ## Proposed Changes\n71: \n72: ### 1. Package Structure\n73: \n74: ```\n75: cmd/cli/\n76: ├── pyproject.toml              # Package metadata, dependencies, console script\n77: ├── agentcube/\n78: │   ├── __init__.py             # Version, exports\n79: │   ├── cli/\n80: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Subpackage marker\n81: │   │   └── main.py             # Typer app, pack command, error handling\n82: │   ├── models/\n83: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Models package\n84: │   │   └── pack_models.py      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n85: │   ├── runtime/\n86: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Re-exports runtimes\n87: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py     # PackRuntime class\n88: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py    # Stub for future AR\n89: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py  # Stub for future AR\n90: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n91: │   │   └── status_runtime.py   # Stub for future AR\n92: │   ├── services/\n93: │   │   ├── __init__.py         # Services package\n94: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py # MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n95: │   │   ├── docker_service.py   # DockerService (stub)\n96: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py     # KubernetesProvider (stub)\n97: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # AgentCubeProvider (stub)\n98: │   └── operations/\n99: │       └── __init__.py         # Placeholder\n100: ├── examples/\n101: │   ├── hello-agent/\n102: │   │   └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n103: │   └── math-agent/\n104: │       └── main.py             # Example Python agent\n105: └── tests/\n106:     ├── __init__.py\n107:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py    # PackRuntime unit tests\n108:     ├── test_metadata_service.py # MetadataService tests\n109:     └── fixtures/\n110:         ├── valid_python_agent/     # Valid Python workspace fixture\n111:         └── valid_java_agent/       # Valid Java workspace fixture\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### 2. pyproject.toml\n115: \n116: ```toml\n117: [build-system]\n118: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n119: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n120: \n121: [project]\n122: name = \"agentcube-cli\"\n123: version = \"0.1.0\"\n124: description = \"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\"\n125: readme = \"README.md\"\n126: license = {text = \"Apache-2.0\"}\n127: authors = [\n128:     {name = \"AgentCube Community\", email = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"}\n129: ]\n130: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n131: classifiers = [\n132:     \"Development Status :: 3 - Alpha\",\n133:     \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n134:     \"License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License\",\n135:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n136:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n137:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n138:     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n139: ]\n140: \n141: dependencies = [\n142:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n143:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n144:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n145:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n146:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n147:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n148:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n149:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n150:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n151: ]\n152: \n153: [project.optional-dependencies]\n154: k8s = [\n155:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n156: ]\n157: dev = [\n158:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n159:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n160:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n161:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n162:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n163:     \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n164:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n165: ]\n166: test = [\n167:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n168:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n169:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n170:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n171:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n172: ]\n173: \n174: [project.scripts]\n175: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n176: \n177: [tool.setuptools]\n178: packages = [\"agentcube\", \"agentcube.cli\", \"agentcube.runtime\", \"agentcube.operations\", \"agentcube.services\"]\n179: \n180: [tool.setuptools.package-data]\n181: agentcube = [\"py.typed\"]\n182: \n183: [tool.pytest.ini_options]\n184: asyncio_mode = \"auto\"\n185: testpaths = [\"tests\"]\n186: \n187: [tool.ruff]\n188: line-length = 100\n189: target-version = \"py310\"\n190: \n191: [tool.mypy]\n192: python_version = \"3.10\"\n193: strict = true\n194: warn_return_any = true\n195: warn_unused_ignores = true\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### 3. AgentMetadata Model\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: # agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\n202: \"\"\"Agent metadata service and models.\"\"\"\n203: \n204: from __future__ import annotations\n205: \n206: from pathlib import Path\n207: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n208: \n209: import yaml\n210: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n211: \n212: \n213: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n214:     \"\"\"Agent metadata model for agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n215: \n216:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n217:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n218:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n219:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n220:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n221:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n222:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n223:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n224:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n225:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n226:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n227:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n228:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n229:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n230:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n231:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n232:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n233:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n234:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n235:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n236:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n237:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n238: \n239:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n240:     @classmethod\n241:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n242:         if v.lower() not in [\"python\", \"java\"]:\n243:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'\")\n244:         return v.lower()\n245: \n246:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n247:     @classmethod\n248:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n249:         if v.lower() not in [\"local\", \"cloud\"]:\n250:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'\")\n251:         return v.lower()\n252: \n253:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n254:     @classmethod\n255:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n256:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n257:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n258:         return v\n259: \n260: \n261: class MetadataService:\n262:     \"\"\"Service for loading and saving agent metadata.\"\"\"\n263: \n264:     METADATA_FILES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n265: \n266:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n267:         self.verbose = verbose\n268: \n269:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n270:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace directory.\"\"\"\n271:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n272:             metadata_file = workspace_path / filename\n273:             if metadata_file.exists():\n274:                 with open(metadata_file, \"r\") as f:\n275:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n276:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n277: \n278:         raise FileNotFoundError(\n279:             f\"No metadata file found. Expected one of: {', '.join(self.METADATA_FILES)}\"\n280:         )\n281: \n282:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n283:         \"\"\"Save metadata to workspace directory.\"\"\"\n284:         metadata_file = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n285:         with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n286:             yaml.dump(\n287:                 metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n288:                 f,\n289:                 default_flow_style=False,\n290:                 indent=2,\n291:                 sort_keys=False,\n292:             )\n293: \n294:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n295:         \"\"\"Update metadata with provided fields.\"\"\"\n296:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n297:         updated_data = metadata.model_dump()\n298:         updated_data.update(updates)\n299:         updated_metadata = AgentMetadata(**updated_data)\n300:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, updated_metadata)\n301:         return updated_metadata\n302: \n303:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n304:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\"\"\"\n305:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n306: \n307:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n308:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n309:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n310:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n311: \n312:         return True\n313: \n314:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n315:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n316:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n317:         if not py_files:\n318:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n319: \n320:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n321:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n322:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n323:         if not pom_xml.exists():\n324:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ### 4. MetadataOptions Dataclass\n328: \n329: ```python\n330: # agentcube/models/pack_models.py\n331: \"\"\"Metadata options for CLI option parsing.\"\"\"\n332: \n333: from __future__ import annotations\n334: \n335: from dataclasses import dataclass\n336: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n337: \n338: \n339: @dataclass\n340: class MetadataOptions:\n341:     \"\"\"Options for metadata overrides from CLI.\"\"\"\n342: \n343:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n344:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n345:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n346:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n347:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n348:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n349:     description: Optional[str] = None\n350:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n351:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n352:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n353:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n354:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n355:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n356:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n357:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n358: \n359:     @classmethod\n360:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n361:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from CLI options dict.\"\"\"\n362:         return cls(\n363:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\"),\n364:             language=options.get(\"language\"),\n365:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\"),\n366:             port=options.get(\"port\"),\n367:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\"),\n368:             requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n369:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n370:             workload_manager_url=options.get(\"workload_manager_url\", \"\"),\n371:             router_url=options.get(\"router_url\", \"\"),\n372:             readiness_probe_path=options.get(\"readiness_probe_path\", \"\"),\n373:             readiness_probe_port=options.get(\"readiness_probe_port\", 8080),\n374:             registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\", \"\"),\n375:             registry_username=options.get(\"registry_username\", \"\"),\n376:             registry_password=options.get(\"registry_password\", \"\"),\n377:             agent_endpoint=options.get(\"agent_endpoint\", \"\"),\n378:         )\n379: ```\n380: \n381: ### 5. PackRuntime Implementation\n382: \n383: ```python\n384: # agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py\n385: \"\"\"PackRuntime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n386: \n387: from __future__ import annotations\n388: \n389: import logging\n390: import shutil\n391: from pathlib import Path\n392: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n393: \n394: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n395: from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n396: \n397: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n398: \n399: \n400: class PackRuntime:\n401:     \"\"\"Runtime for packaging agent workspaces.\"\"\"\n402: \n403:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n404:         self.verbose = verbose\n405:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n406:         if verbose:\n407:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n408: \n409:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n410:         \"\"\"Package an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n411:         logger.debug(f\"Packing workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n412: \n413:         # Validate workspace structure\n414:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n415: \n416:         # Load or create metadata\n417:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n418: \n419:         # Apply CLI option overrides\n420:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n421: \n422:         # Validate language compatibility\n423:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n424: \n425:         # Process dependencies\n426:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n427: \n428:         # Generate Dockerfile\n429:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n430: \n431:         # Update pack metadata\n432:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n433: \n434:         # Prepare output path\n435:         output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n436: \n437:         logger.info(f\"Successfully packed workspace to: {output_path}\")\n438: \n439:         return {\n440:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n441:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n442:             \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n443:             \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n444:             \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n445:         }\n446: \n447:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n448:         \"\"\"Validate that workspace path exists and is a directory.\"\"\"\n449:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n450:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n451:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n452:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n453: \n454:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n455:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new one.\"\"\"\n456:         try:\n457:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n458:             logger.debug(f\"Loaded existing metadata: {metadata.agent_name}\")\n459:             return metadata\n460:         except FileNotFoundError:\n461:             logger.debug(\"No existing metadata found, creating new one\")\n462:             return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n463: \n464:     def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n465:         \"\"\"Create default metadata for a workspace.\"\"\"\n466:         language = options.get(\"language\", \"python\")\n467:         entrypoint = options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, language)\n468: \n469:         return AgentMetadata(\n470:             agent_name=options.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n471:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n472:             language=language,\n473:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n474:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n475:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n476:         )\n477: \n478:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n479:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n480:         updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n481: \n482:         for field in [\n483:             \"agent_name\", \"description\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\",\n484:             \"build_mode\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n485:             \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n486:             \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\",\n487:             \"agent_endpoint\",\n488:         ]:\n489:             value = options.get(field)\n490:             if value is not None and value != \"\":\n491:                 updates[field] = value\n492: \n493:         if updates:\n494:             logger.debug(f\"Applying metadata overrides: {updates}\")\n495:             metadata_dict = metadata.model_dump()\n496:             metadata_dict.update(updates)\n497:             metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata_dict)\n498: \n499:         return metadata\n500: \n501:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n502:         \"\"\"Validate language-specific requirements.\"\"\"\n503:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n504:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n505:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n506:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n507: \n508:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n509:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace.\"\"\"\n510:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n511:         if not py_files:\n512:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n513: \n514:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n515:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace.\"\"\"\n516:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n517:         if not pom_xml.exists():\n518:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in workspace\")\n519: \n520:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n521:         \"\"\"Process language-specific dependencies.\"\"\"\n522:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n523:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n524:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n525:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n526: \n527:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n528:         \"\"\"Process Python dependencies from requirements.txt.\"\"\"\n529:         requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n530:         if requirements_file.exists():\n531:             logger.debug(f\"Found requirements.txt: {requirements_file}\")\n532:         else:\n533:             logger.debug(\"No requirements.txt found\")\n534: \n535:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n536:         \"\"\"Process Java dependencies from pom.xml.\"\"\"\n537:         pom_xml = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n538:         if pom_xml.exists():\n539:             logger.debug(f\"Found pom.xml: {pom_xml}\")\n540:         else:\n541:             logger.debug(\"No pom.xml found\")\n542: \n543:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n544:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for the workspace.\"\"\"\n545:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n546:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n547:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n548:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n549:         else:\n550:             logger.warning(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n551:             return None\n552: \n553:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n554:         with open(dockerfile_path, \"w\") as f:\n555:             f.write(content)\n556: \n557:         logger.info(f\"Generated Dockerfile: {dockerfile_path}\")\n558:         return dockerfile_path\n559: \n560:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n561:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Python agent.\"\"\"\n562:         return f\"\"\"FROM python:3.11-slim\n563: \n564: WORKDIR /app\n565: \n566: # Copy requirements first for better caching\n567: COPY requirements.txt .\n568: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n569: \n570: # Copy application code\n571: COPY . .\n572: \n573: # Expose port\n574: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n575: \n576: # Run the agent\n577: ENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n578: \"\"\"\n579: \n580:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n581:         \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile for Java agent.\"\"\"\n582:         return f\"\"\"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n583: \n584: WORKDIR /app\n585: \n586: # Copy pom.xml and download dependencies\n587: COPY pom.xml .\n588: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n589: \n590: # Copy source code and build\n591: COPY src ./src\n592: RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n593: \n594: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n595: \n596: WORKDIR /app\n597: \n598: # Copy built artifact\n599: COPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n600: \n601: # Expose port\n602: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n603: \n604: # Run the agent\n605: ENTRYPOINT {metadata.entrypoint}\n606: \"\"\"\n607: \n608:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n609:         \"\"\"Update metadata after packaging.\"\"\"\n610:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n611:         logger.debug(\"Updated pack metadata\")\n612: \n613:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n614:         \"\"\"Prepare output path for packaged workspace.\"\"\"\n615:         if output_path:\n616:             output = Path(output_path)\n617:             output.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n618:             shutil.copytree(workspace_path, output, dirs_exist_ok=True)\n619:             return output\n620:         return workspace_path\n621: \n622:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n623:         \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace.\"\"\"\n624:         if language == \"python\":\n625:             # Look for main.py or app.py\n626:             for name in [\"main.py\", \"app.py\"]:\n627:                 if (workspace_path / name).exists():\n628:                     return f\"python {name}\"\n629:             # Default to first .py file\n630:             py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n631:             if py_files:\n632:                 return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n633:             return \"python main.py\"\n634:         elif language == \"java\":\n635:             return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n636:         return \"python main.py\"\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ### 6. CLI Main Entry Point\n640: \n641: ```python\n642: # agentcube/cli/main.py\n643: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI main entry point.\"\"\"\n644: \n645: from __future__ import annotations\n646: \n647: import json\n648: import logging\n649: import sys\n650: from pathlib import Path\n651: from typing import List, Optional\n652: \n653: import typer\n654: from rich.console import Console\n655: from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n656: \n657: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n658: \n659: console = Console()\n660: \n661: app = typer.Typer(\n662:     name=\"agentcube\",\n663:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\",\n664:     no_args_is_help=True,\n665:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n666:     add_completion=False,\n667: )\n668: \n669: \n670: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n671:     \"\"\"Version callback.\"\"\"\n672:     if value:\n673:         from agentcube import __version__\n674:         console.print(f\"[bold]AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version:[/bold] {__version__}\")\n675:         raise typer.Exit()\n676: \n677: \n678: @app.callback()\n679: def main(\n680:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n681:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n682:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n683:     ),\n684:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n685: ) -> None:\n686:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n687:     if verbose:\n688:         logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n689: \n690: \n691: @app.command()\n692: def pack(\n693:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n694:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n695:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n696:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n697:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n698:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n699:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n700:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n701:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n702: ) -> None:\n703:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace for deployment.\"\"\"\n704:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n705: \n706:     with Progress(\n707:         SpinnerColumn(),\n708:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n709:         console=console,\n710:     ) as progress:\n711:         progress.add_task(description=\"Packaging workspace...\", total=None)\n712: \n713:         try:\n714:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n715:             result = runtime.pack(\n716:                 workspace_path,\n717:                 agent_name=agent_name,\n718:                 language=language,\n719:                 entrypoint=entrypoint,\n720:                 port=port,\n721:                 build_mode=build_mode,\n722:                 description=description,\n723:                 output=output,\n724:             )\n725: \n726:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Successfully packed agent: [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]\")\n727:             console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n728:             console.print(f\"  Metadata: {result['metadata_path']}\")\n729:             if result.get('dockerfile_path'):\n730:                 console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n731:             if result.get('output_path'):\n732:                 console.print(f\"  Output: {result['output_path']}\")\n733: \n734:         except Exception as e:\n735:             _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n736: \n737: \n738: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n739:     \"\"\"Handle and display errors.\"\"\"\n740:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n741:     if verbose:\n742:         import traceback\n743:         traceback.print_exc()\n744:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n745: \n746: \n747: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n748:     app()\n749: ```\n750: \n751: ### 7. Package Exports\n752: \n753: ```python\n754: # agentcube/__init__.py\n755: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI package.\"\"\"\n756: \n757: __version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n758: __author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"\n759: __email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n760: \n761: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n762: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n763: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n764: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n765: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n766: \n767: __all__ = [\n768:     \"app\",\n769:     \"PackRuntime\",\n770:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n771:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n772:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n773: ]\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ```python\n777: # agentcube/runtime/__init__.py\n778: \"\"\"Runtime module.\"\"\"\n779: \n780: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n781: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n782: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n783: from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime\n784: from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime\n785: \n786: __all__ = [\n787:     \"PackRuntime\",\n788:     \"BuildRuntime\",\n789:     \"PublishRuntime\",\n790:     \"InvokeRuntime\",\n791:     \"StatusRuntime\",\n792: ]\n793: ```\n794: \n795: ### 8. Example Agents\n796: \n797: ```python\n798: # examples/hello-agent/main.py\n799: \"\"\"Hello Agent example.\"\"\"\n800: \n801: from flask import Flask, jsonify\n802: \n803: app = Flask(__name__)\n804: \n805: \n806: @app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\n807: def health():\n808:     return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n809: \n810: \n811: @app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\n812: def invoke():\n813:     return jsonify({\"message\": \"Hello from AgentCube!\"})\n814: \n815: \n816: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n817:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n818: ```\n819: \n820: ```python\n821: # examples/math-agent/main.py\n822: \"\"\"Math Agent example.\"\"\"\n823: \n824: from flask import Flask, jsonify, request\n825: \n826: app = Flask(__name__)\n827: \n828: \n829: @app.route(\"/health\", methods=[\"GET\"])\n830: def health():\n831:     return jsonify({\"status\": \"healthy\"})\n832: \n833: \n834: @app.route(\"/invoke\", methods=[\"POST\"])\n835: def invoke():\n836:     data = request.get_json() or {}\n837:     operation = data.get(\"operation\", \"add\")\n838:     a = data.get(\"a\", 0)\n839:     b = data.get(\"b\", 0)\n840: \n841:     if operation == \"add\":\n842:         result = a + b\n843:     elif operation == \"subtract\":\n844:         result = a - b\n845:     elif operation == \"multiply\":\n846:         result = a * b\n847:     elif operation == \"divide\":\n848:         result = a / b if b != 0 else {\"error\": \"Division by zero\"}\n849:     else:\n850:         result = {\"error\": f\"Unknown operation: {operation}\"}\n851: \n852:     return jsonify({\"result\": result})\n853: \n854: \n855: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n856:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n857: ```\n858: \n859: ### 9. Unit Tests\n860: \n861: ```python\n862: # tests/test_pack_runtime.py\n863: \"\"\"Tests for PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n864: \n865: import tempfile\n866: from pathlib import Path\n867: \n868: import pytest\n869: \n870: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n871: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata\n872: \n873: \n874: @pytest.fixture\n875: def python_workspace():\n876:     \"\"\"Create a temporary Python workspace.\"\"\"\n877:     with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n878:         workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n879:         # Create main.py\n880:         (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\n881: from flask import Flask\n882: app = Flask(__name__)\n883: \n884: @app.route(\"/health\")\n885: def health():\n886:     return {\"status\": \"healthy\"}\n887: \n888: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n889:     app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8080)\n890: \"\"\")\n891:         # Create requirements.txt\n892:         (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"flask>=2.0.0\\n\")\n893:         yield workspace\n894: \n895: \n896: class TestPackRuntime:\n897:     \"\"\"Test PackRuntime.\"\"\"\n898: \n899:     def test_pack_success(self, python_workspace):\n900:         \"\"\"Test successful packaging.\"\"\"\n901:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n902:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n903: \n904:         assert result[\"agent_name\"] == python_workspace.name\n905:         assert result[\"workspace_path\"] == str(python_workspace)\n906:         assert Path(result[\"metadata_path\"]).exists()\n907:         assert Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"]).exists()\n908: \n909:     def test_pack_validate_missing_workspace(self):\n910:         \"\"\"Test validation with missing workspace.\"\"\"\n911:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n912:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"does not exist\"):\n913:             runtime.pack(Path(\"/nonexistent/path\"))\n914: \n915:     def test_pack_validate_no_python_files(self, tmp_path):\n916:         \"\"\"Test validation with no Python files.\"\"\"\n917:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n918:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No Python files found\"):\n919:             runtime.pack(tmp_path)\n920: \n921:     def test_pack_infer_entrypoint(self, python_workspace):\n922:         \"\"\"Test entrypoint inference.\"\"\"\n923:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n924:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n925: \n926:         metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n927:         metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n928:         assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n929: \n930:     def test_pack_override_options(self, python_workspace):\n931:         \"\"\"Test CLI option overrides.\"\"\"\n932:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n933:         result = runtime.pack(\n934:             python_workspace,\n935:             agent_name=\"custom-agent\",\n936:             language=\"python\",\n937:             entrypoint=\"python custom.py\",\n938:             port=9090,\n939:             build_mode=\"cloud\",\n940:         )\n941: \n942:         metadata_path = Path(result[\"metadata_path\"])\n943:         metadata = AgentMetadata.model_validate(__import__(\"yaml\").safe_load(metadata_path.read_text()))\n944:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"custom-agent\"\n945:         assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python custom.py\"\n946:         assert metadata.port == 9090\n947:         assert metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"\n948: \n949:     def test_generate_python_dockerfile(self, python_workspace):\n950:         \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n951:         runtime = PackRuntime()\n952:         result = runtime.pack(python_workspace)\n953: \n954:         dockerfile_path = Path(result[\"dockerfile_path\"])\n955:         content = dockerfile_path.read_text()\n956: \n957:         assert \"FROM python:3.11-slim\" in content\n958:         assert \"EXPOSE 8080\" in content\n959:         assert \"ENTRYPOINT python main.py\" in content\n960: ```\n961: \n962: ```python\n963: # tests/test_metadata_service.py\n964: \"\"\"Tests for MetadataService.\"\"\"\n965: \n966: import tempfile\n967: from pathlib import Path\n968: \n969: import pytest\n970: import yaml\n971: \n972: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n973: \n974: \n975: class TestMetadataService:\n976:     \"\"\"Test MetadataService.\"\"\"\n977: \n978:     def test_load_metadata_success(self, tmp_path):\n979:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata.\"\"\"\n980:         # Create metadata file\n981:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n982:         metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n983:             \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n984:             \"language\": \"python\",\n985:             \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n986:             \"port\": 8080,\n987:         }))\n988: \n989:         service = MetadataService()\n990:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n991: \n992:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n993:         assert metadata.language == \"python\"\n994: \n995:     def test_load_metadata_fallback(self, tmp_path):\n996:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata with fallback filenames.\"\"\"\n997:         # Create agent.yaml (fallback)\n998:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent.yaml\"\n999:         metadata_file.write_text(yaml.dump({\n1000:             \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n1001:             \"language\": \"python\",\n1002:             \"entrypoint\": \"python main.py\",\n1003:             \"port\": 8080,\n1004:         }))\n1005: \n1006:         service = MetadataService()\n1007:         metadata = service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n1008: \n1009:         assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n1010: \n1011:     def test_load_metadata_not_found(self, tmp_path):\n1012:         \"\"\"Test loading metadata when file doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n1013:         service = MetadataService()\n1014:         with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError):\n1015:             service.load_metadata(tmp_path)\n1016: \n1017:     def test_save_metadata(self, tmp_path):\n1018:         \"\"\"Test saving metadata.\"\"\"\n1019:         service = MetadataService()\n1020:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n1021:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n1022:             language=\"python\",\n1023:             entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1024:             port=8080,\n1025:         )\n1026: \n1027:         service.save_metadata(tmp_path, metadata)\n1028: \n1029:         metadata_file = tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n1030:         assert metadata_file.exists()\n1031: \n1032:         saved_data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n1033:         assert saved_data[\"agent_name\"] == \"test-agent\"\n1034: \n1035:     def test_validate_language(self):\n1036:         \"\"\"Test language validation.\"\"\"\n1037:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported language\"):\n1038:             AgentMetadata(\n1039:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1040:                 language=\"javascript\",\n1041:                 entrypoint=\"node main.js\",\n1042:             )\n1043: \n1044:     def test_validate_build_mode(self):\n1045:         \"\"\"Test build mode validation.\"\"\"\n1046:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Unsupported build mode\"):\n1047:             AgentMetadata(\n1048:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1049:                 language=\"python\",\n1050:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1051:                 build_mode=\"hybrid\",\n1052:             )\n1053: \n1054:     def test_validate_port_range(self):\n1055:         \"\"\"Test port range validation.\"\"\"\n1056:         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Port must be between\"):\n1057:             AgentMetadata(\n1058:                 agent_name=\"test\",\n1059:                 language=\"python\",\n1060:                 entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n1061:                 port=70000,\n1062:             )\n1063: ```\n1064: \n1065: ### 10. Stubs for Future Commands\n1066: \n1067: ```python\n1068: # agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py\n1069: \"\"\"BuildRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1070: \n1071: from __future__ import annotations\n1072: \n1073: import logging\n1074: from pathlib import Path\n1075: from typing import Any, Dict\n1076: \n1077: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1078: \n1079: \n1080: class BuildRuntime:\n1081:     \"\"\"Runtime for building agent images.\"\"\"\n1082: \n1083:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1084:         self.verbose = verbose\n1085:         if verbose:\n1086:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1087: \n1088:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1089:         \"\"\"Build an agent image.\"\"\"\n1090:         raise NotImplementedError(\"build command not yet implemented\")\n1091: ```\n1092: \n1093: ```python\n1094: # agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py\n1095: \"\"\"PublishRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1096: \n1097: from __future__ import annotations\n1098: \n1099: import logging\n1100: from pathlib import Path\n1101: from typing import Any, Dict\n1102: \n1103: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1104: \n1105: \n1106: class PublishRuntime:\n1107:     \"\"\"Runtime for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n1108: \n1109:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1110:         self.verbose = verbose\n1111:         self.provider = provider\n1112:         if verbose:\n1113:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1114: \n1115:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1116:         \"\"\"Publish an agent.\"\"\"\n1117:         raise NotImplementedError(\"publish command not yet implemented\")\n1118: ```\n1119: \n1120: ```python\n1121: # agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n1122: \"\"\"InvokeRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1123: \n1124: from __future__ import annotations\n1125: \n1126: import logging\n1127: from pathlib import Path\n1128: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1129: \n1130: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1131: \n1132: \n1133: class InvokeRuntime:\n1134:     \"\"\"Runtime for invoking agents.\"\"\"\n1135: \n1136:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1137:         self.verbose = verbose\n1138:         self.provider = provider\n1139:         if verbose:\n1140:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1141: \n1142:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n1143:         \"\"\"Invoke an agent.\"\"\"\n1144:         raise NotImplementedError(\"invoke command not yet implemented\")\n1145: ```\n1146: \n1147: ```python\n1148: # agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n1149: \"\"\"StatusRuntime stub.\"\"\"\n1150: \n1151: from __future__ import annotations\n1152: \n1153: import logging\n1154: from pathlib import Path\n1155: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1156: \n1157: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1158: \n1159: \n1160: class StatusRuntime:\n1161:     \"\"\"Runtime for getting agent status.\"\"\"\n1162: \n1163:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1164:         self.verbose = verbose\n1165:         self.provider = provider\n1166:         if verbose:\n1167:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1168: \n1169:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1170:         \"\"\"Get agent status.\"\"\"\n1171:         raise NotImplementedError(\"status command not yet implemented\")\n1172: ```\n1173: \n1174: ```python\n1175: # agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n1176: \"\"\"DockerService stub.\"\"\"\n1177: \n1178: from __future__ import annotations\n1179: \n1180: import logging\n1181: from pathlib import Path\n1182: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1183: \n1184: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1185: \n1186: \n1187: class DockerService:\n1188:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n1189: \n1190:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1191:         self.verbose = verbose\n1192:         if verbose:\n1193:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1194: \n1195:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n1196:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available.\"\"\"\n1197:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n1198: \n1199:     def build_image(\n1200:         self,\n1201:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n1202:         context_path: Path,\n1203:         image_name: str,\n1204:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n1205:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1206:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n1207:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n1208:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Docker service not yet implemented\")\n1209: ```\n1210: \n1211: ```python\n1212: # agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\n1213: \"\"\"KubernetesProvider stub.\"\"\"\n1214: \n1215: from __future__ import annotations\n1216: \n1217: import logging\n1218: from pathlib import Path\n1219: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1220: \n1221: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1222: \n1223: \n1224: class KubernetesProvider:\n1225:     \"\"\"Provider for Kubernetes operations.\"\"\"\n1226: \n1227:     def __init__(\n1228:         self,\n1229:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1230:         verbose: bool = False,\n1231:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1232:     ) -> None:\n1233:         self.namespace = namespace\n1234:         self.verbose = verbose\n1235:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1236:         if verbose:\n1237:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1238: \n1239:     def deploy_agent(\n1240:         self,\n1241:         agent_name: str,\n1242:         image_url: str,\n1243:         port: int,\n1244:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1245:         replicas: int = 1,\n1246:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1247:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1248:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1249:         \"\"\"Deploy an agent to Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n1250:         raise NotImplementedError(\"Kubernetes provider not yet implemented\")\n1251: ```\n1252: \n1253: ```python\n1254: # agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\n1255: \"\"\"AgentCubeProvider stub.\"\"\"\n1256: \n1257: from __future__ import annotations\n1258: \n1259: import logging\n1260: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n1261: \n1262: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n1263: \n1264: \n1265: class AgentCubeProvider:\n1266:     \"\"\"Provider for AgentCube CR operations.\"\"\"\n1267: \n1268:     def __init__(\n1269:         self,\n1270:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n1271:         verbose: bool = False,\n1272:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n1273:     ) -> None:\n1274:         self.namespace = namespace\n1275:         self.verbose = verbose\n1276:         self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n1277:         if verbose:\n1278:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n1279: \n1280:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n1281:         self,\n1282:         agent_name: str,\n1283:         image_url: str,\n1284:         port: int,\n1285:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n1286:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n1287:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1288:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n1289:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n1290:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n1291:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1292:         \"\"\"Deploy an AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n1293:         raise NotImplementedError(\"AgentCube provider not yet implemented\")\n1294: ```\n1295: \n1296: ## Impact Analysis\n1297: \n1298: ### Dependencies\n1299: \n1300: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n1301: |---------|---------|---------|\n1302: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich support |\n1303: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Data validation with BaseModel |\n1304: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML parsing and dumping |\n1305: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future commands |\n1306: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n1307: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Terminal formatting |\n1308: | `packaging` | `>=23.0` | Version parsing |\n1309: | `importlib-resources` | `>=6.0.0` | Resource file access |\n1310: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic versioning |\n1311: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Optional K8s client (optional dependency) |\n1312: | `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Testing (dev dependency) |\n1313: | `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n1314: | `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n1315: \n1316: ### Files to Create\n1317: \n1318: ```\n1319: cmd/cli/\n1320: ├── pyproject.toml\n1321: ├── README.md\n1322: ├── agentcube/\n1323: │   ├── __init__.py\n1324: │   ├── cli/\n1325: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1326: │   │   └── main.py\n1327: │   ├── models/\n1328: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1329: │   │   └── pack_models.py\n1330: │   ├── runtime/\n1331: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1332: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n1333: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n1334: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n1335: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n1336: │   │   └── status_runtime.py\n1337: │   ├── services/\n1338: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n1339: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n1340: │   │   ├── docker_service.py\n1341: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n1342: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n1343: │   └── operations/\n1344: │       └── __init__.py\n1345: ├── examples/\n1346: │   ├── hello-agent/\n1347: │   │   ├── main.py\n1348: │   │   └── requirements.txt\n1349: │   └── math-agent/\n1350: │       ├── main.py\n1351: │       └── requirements.txt\n1352: └── tests/\n1353:     ├── __init__.py\n1354:     ├── conftest.py\n1355:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n1356:     ├── test_metadata_service.py\n1357:     └── fixtures/\n1358:         ├── __init__.py\n1359:         ├── valid_python_agent/\n1360:         └── valid_java_agent/\n1361: ```\n1362: \n1363: ### Affected Components\n1364: \n1365: 1. **Build System**: Need to add Python package build to CI/CD\n1366: 2. **Distribution**: Package publishable to PyPI\n1367: 3. **Documentation**: CLI usage documentation needed\n1368: 4. **Examples**: Example agents for testing and demonstration\n1369: \n1370: ### Backward Compatibility\n1371: \n1372: - All code is new with no existing API surface\n1373: - Metadata file format follows spec with fallback support\n1374: - CLI options use sensible defaults\n1375: \n1376: ### Risk Assessment\n1377: \n1378: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n1379: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n1380: | Pydantic v2 API changes | Low | Low | Pin version >=2.0.0, follow migration guide |\n1381: | Docker SDK compatibility | Low | Low | Pin version >=6.0.0, test with multiple Docker versions |\n1382: | YAML parsing edge cases | Low | Low | Comprehensive test coverage for metadata loading |\n1383: | Python version compatibility | Low | Medium | Test against Python 3.10, 3.11, 3.12 |\n1384: | Path handling across OS | Medium | Medium | Use pathlib throughout, test on Linux/MacOS |\n1385: \n1386: ## Alternatives Considered\n1387: \n1388: ### Alternative 1: Click CLI Framework\n1389: \n1390: **Approach**: Use Click instead of Typer for CLI implementation\n1391: \n1392: **Pros**:\n1393: - More mature and widely adopted\n1394: - Larger community and ecosystem\n1395: - More flexible for complex CLI structures\n1396: \n1397: **Cons**:\n1398: - More boilerplate code required\n1399: - Less modern API design\n1400: - Rich integration requires additional setup\n1401: \n1402: **Decision**: Typer provides better developer experience with type hints and built-in Rich support.\n1403: \n1404: ### Alternative 2: Single Metadata File Name\n1405: \n1406: **Approach**: Only support `agent_metadata.yaml` without fallbacks\n1407: \n1408: **Pros**:\n1409: - Simpler implementation\n1410: - Clear canonical filename\n1411: - No ambiguity\n1412: \n1413: **Cons**:\n1414: - Breaking change if filename needs to evolve\n1415: - No backward compatibility with existing agents\n1416: - Less flexible for users\n1417: \n1418: **Decision**: Support fallback filenames (`agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`) for better compatibility.\n1419: \n1420: ### Alternative 3: No Dockerfile Generation\n1421: \n1422: **Approach**: Require users to provide their own Dockerfile\n1423: \n1424: **Pros**:\n1425: - More flexibility for custom Dockerfiles\n1426: - No opinionated Dockerfile templates\n1427: - Simpler implementation\n1428: \n1429: **Cons**:\n1430: - Higher barrier to entry for users\n1431: - Inconsistent Dockerfile quality\n1432: - More manual work for simple use cases\n1433: \n1434: **Decision**: Generate sensible default Dockerfiles while allowing user overrides.\n1435: \n1436: ## Testing Strategy\n1437: \n1438: ### Unit Tests\n1439: \n1440: 1. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_success**: Successful packaging with Python workspace\n1441: 2. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_missing_workspace**: Validation with missing directory\n1442: 3. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_no_python_files**: Validation with no Python files\n1443: 4. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_infer_entrypoint**: Entrypoint inference from files\n1444: 5. **TestPackRuntime.test_pack_override_options**: CLI option overrides\n1445: 6. **TestPackRuntime.test_generate_python_dockerfile**: Dockerfile content verification\n1446: 7. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_success**: Load from primary filename\n1447: 8. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_fallback**: Load from fallback filename\n1448: 9. **TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_not_found**: FileNotFoundError on missing\n1449: 10. **TestMetadataService.test_save_metadata**: Save and verify content\n1450: 11. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_language**: Language validator\n1451: 12. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_build_mode**: Build mode validator\n1452: 13. **TestMetadataService.test_validate_port_range**: Port range validator\n1453: \n1454: ### Integration Tests\n1455: \n1456: 1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n1457: 2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n1458: 3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n1459: 4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n1460: \n1461: ### Test Fixtures\n1462: \n1463: - `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n1464: - `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n1465: \n1466: ## Acceptance Criteria\n1467: \n1468: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version and exits\n1469: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack` command with all specified options\n1470: - [ ] Workspace validation for Python (requires .py files) and Java (requires pom.xml)\n1471: - [ ] Metadata loading with fallback filenames (`agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`)\n1472: - [ ] Metadata saving to `agent_metadata.yaml` in correct YAML format\n1473: - [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n1474: - [ ] Dockerfile generation for Python agents\n1475: - [ ] Dockerfile generation for Java agents\n1476: - [ ] Entrypoint inference from workspace files\n1477: - [ ] Verbose error handling with traceback\n1478: - [ ] Rich progress spinner during pack operation\n1479: - [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n1480: - [ ] Package installs via `pip install -e .`\n1481: - [ ] Example agents pack successfully\n1482: - [ ] Pydantic validators reject invalid language/build_mode/port values\n1483: \n1484: ## References\n1485: \n1486: - `cli-toolkit/spec.md`: CLI Toolkit Specification\n1487: - `cli-toolkit/design.md`: CLI Toolkit Design\n1488: - `python-sdk/design.md`: Python SDK Design\n1489: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n1490: - Pydantic v2 Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n1491: - Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 1491 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI Pack Command\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `pack` command for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `pack` command validates and prepares agent workspaces, merges CLI overrides into metadata, generates Dockerfiles, and reports paths. This is the first command in the Python CLI toolkit that provides developer-friendly tooling for packaging AI agents for deployment on AgentCube.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide workspace validation** - Ensure agent workspaces have the required structure and files for the target language (Python/Java)\n2. **Enable metadata management** - Load, merge, and persist agent configuration as YAML\n3. **Generate deployment artifacts** - Create Dockerfiles tailored to the agent's language and dependencies\n4. **Support development workflows** - Enable developers to package agents with CLI overrides before building and publishing\n\nThis implementation builds upon the Python SDK design (`python-sdk/design.md`) and CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`).\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775865404353,"end":1775865404388}}}}
