{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865415185,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d3bbe0001l19eg2e9gl2w3f","messageID":"msg_d79d3b1fc001JlNyV5ffQZ1Vgo","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_dffc6badf22542df994cdf57","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) |\n8: | Module | `cmd` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Version Package (`pkg/version/version.go`)\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/version/version.go`\n18:   - Define package `version` with required imports\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define package-level variables in `pkg/version/version.go`\n21:   - `Version string` (default: \"0.0.0\")\n22:   - `GitCommit string` (default: \"unknown\")\n23:   - `BuildDate string` (default: \"unknown\")\n24:   - `GoVersion string` (default: \"unknown\")\n25: \n26: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Info` struct in `pkg/version/version.go`\n27:   - Fields: `Version`, `GitCommit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion` (all string, with json tags)\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Implement `Get() Info` in `pkg/version/version.go`\n30:   - Return Info struct with all version variables\n31: \n32: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `String() string` in `pkg/version/version.go`\n33:   - Return formatted version string (e.g., \"version/gitCommit/buildDate/goVersion\")\n34: \n35: ### Phase 2: CLI Common Configuration (`pkg/cli/common/config.go`)\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n38:   - Define package `common` with required imports (spf13/viper, k8s.io/client-go/util/homedir, filepath, os)\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `CLIConfig` struct in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n41:   - Fields: `Kubeconfig string`, `Namespace string`, `Timeout int`, `Output string`, `LogLevel string` (all with mapstructure tags)\n42: \n43: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `LoadConfig() (*CLIConfig, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n44:   - Configure viper with config name \"config\", type \"yaml\"\n45:   - Add config paths: ~/.agentcube, current directory\n46:   - Enable automatic environment variables\n47:   - Set defaults (kubeconfig=\"\", namespace=\"default\", timeout=30, output=\"table\", log-level=\"info\")\n48:   - Handle ConfigFileNotFoundError gracefully\n49:   - Override Kubeconfig with KUBECONFIG env var if set\n50:   - Return config or error\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `GetClientset(config *CLIConfig) (*versioned.Clientset, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/config.go`\n53:   - Build kubeconfig from flags/env\n54:   - Create and return typed clientset\n55:   - Return error on failure\n56: \n57: ### Phase 3: CLI Output Helpers (`pkg/cli/common/output.go`)\n58: \n59: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n60:   - Define package `common` with required imports (encoding/json, fmt, os, gopkg.in/yaml.v3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `PrintObject(obj runtime.Object, format string) error` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n63:   - Switch on format: json, yaml, table\n64:   - JSON: encode with indentation\n65:   - YAML: marshal to JSON first, then convert to YAML\n66:   - Table: return error (not supported for generic objects)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `PrintTable(headers []string, rows [][]string)` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n69:   - Calculate column widths\n70:   - Print formatted table with proper alignment\n71: \n72: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `jsonToYAML(data []byte) ([]byte, error)` in `pkg/cli/common/output.go`\n73:   - Convert JSON to YAML using yaml.v3\n74: \n75: ### Phase 4: picod Binary (`cmd/picod/main.go`)\n76: \n77: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `cmd/picod/main.go`\n78:   - Define package `main` with required imports (flag, net/http, os, strings)\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Define CLI flags in `cmd/picod/main.go`\n81:   - `-port` (int, default: 8080)\n82:   - `-workspace` (string, default: \".\")\n83:   - `-auth` (string, default: \"none\")\n84:   - `-public-key` (string, default: \"\")\n85:   - `-skip-paths` (string, default: \"/health\")\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `main()` in `cmd/picod/main.go`\n88:   - Parse flags\n89:   - Load config from flags and env\n90:   - Get SANDBOX_ID from env\n91:   - Create PicoD instance with functional options\n92:   - Setup HTTP server with optional JWT middleware\n93:   - Start server on specified port\n94:   - Handle server errors with klog\n95: \n96: ### Phase 5: agentcube CLI Root (`cmd/agentcube/main.go`)\n97: \n98: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n99:   - Define package `main` with required imports (os, spf13/cobra)\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewRootCommand() *cobra.Command` in `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n102:   - Use: \"agentcube\"\n103:   - Short/Long description\n104:   - Add subcommands: agentruntime, codeinterpreter, version, completion\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `main()` in `cmd/agentcube/main.go`\n107:   - Execute root command\n108:   - Exit with code 1 on error\n109: \n110: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Create `cmd/agentcube/version.go`\n111:   - Implement versionCmd (cobra.Command)\n112:   - Print version info from pkg/version.Get()\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Create `cmd/agentcube/completion.go`\n115:   - Implement completionCmd (cobra.Command)\n116:   - Support bash, zsh, fish, powershell\n117:   - Generate completion scripts\n118: \n119: ### Phase 6: agentruntime Commands (`pkg/cli/agentruntime/`)\n120: \n1