{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865549433,"sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","part":{"id":"prt_d79d3d609001c5zwa4WacAoVs3","messageID":"msg_d79d3c648001D49ZOQyuRKRb37","sessionID":"ses_2862cd73cffeYZbpmgaOX5ACuI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_92ce56d63bf24493968896a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","content":"# AR-020 — CLI Pack Command Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Package Structure Setup\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n  - Define build system (setuptools>=61.0, wheel)\n  - Set project metadata (name, version, description, license, authors)\n  - Specify Python requirement (>=3.10)\n  - Add classifiers for Python versions\n  - Define dependencies (typer, pydantic, pyyaml, httpx, docker, rich, packaging, importlib-resources, semver)\n  - Define optional dependencies (k8s, dev, test)\n  - Configure console script entry point (kubectl-agentcube)\n  - Add tool configurations (setuptools, pytest, ruff, mypy)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Define `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n  - Define `__author__` and `__email__`\n  - Import and export `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n  - Define `__all__` list\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/__init__.py`\n  - Package subpackage marker (can be empty or with docstring)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py`\n  - Package subpackage marker\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n  - Re-export all runtime classes (PackRuntime, BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n  - Define `__all__` list\n\n- [ ] **TASK-006**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n  - Package subpackage marker with docstring\n\n- [ ] **TASK-007**: Create `cmd/cli/agentcube/operations/__init__.py`\n  - Placeholder module with docstring\n\n### Phase 2: Metadata Models (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n  - Define package imports (pathlib, typing, yaml, pydantic)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model in `metadata_service.py`\n  - Field `agent_name: str` (required)\n  - Field `description: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `language: str` (default: \"python\")\n  - Field `entrypoint: str` (required)\n  - Field `port: int` (default: 8080)\n  - Field `build_mode: str` (default: \"local\")\n  - Field `region: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `version: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` (default: None)\n  - Field `auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` (default: None)\n  - Field `requirements_file: Optional[str]` (default: \"requirements.txt\")\n  - Field `registry_url: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `registry_username: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `registry_password: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `agent_endpoint: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `workload_manager_url: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `router_url: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `readiness_probe_path: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `readiness_probe_port: Optional[int]` (default: None)\n  - Field `agent_id: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `session_id: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` (default: None)\n  - Add Field descriptions for all fields\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `validate_language` validator in `AgentMetadata`\n  - Validate language is \"python\" or \"java\" (case-insensitive)\n  - Raise ValueError for unsupported languages\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `validate_build_mode` validator in `AgentMetadata`\n  - Validate build_mode is \"local\" or \"cloud\" (case-insensitive)\n  - Raise ValueError for unsupported modes\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `validate_port` validator in `AgentMetadata`\n  - Validate port is between 1 and 65535\n  - Raise ValueError for invalid port range\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Define `MetadataService` class in `metadata_service.py`\n  - Define `METADATA_FILES` constant: [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n  - Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata` in `MetadataService`\n  - Iterate through METADATA_FILES\n  - Load first existing file with yaml.safe_load\n  - Return AgentMetadata instance\n  - Raise FileNotFoundError if no metadata file found\n\n- [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None` in `MetadataService`\n  - Save to agent_metadata.yaml\n  - Use yaml.dump with default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False\n  - Exclude None fields via model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-018**: Implement `update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata` in `MetadataService`\n  - Load existing metadata\n  - Update with provided fields\n  - Save and return updated metadata\n\n- [ ] **TASK-019**: Implement `validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool` in `MetadataService`\n  - Load metadata\n  - Delegate to language-specific validation\n  - Return True on success\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `_validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)` in `MetadataService`\n  - Check for at least one .py file in workspace\n  - Raise ValueError if no Python files found\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `_validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)` in `MetadataService`\n  - Check for pom.xml in workspace\n  - Raise ValueError if pom.xml not found\n\n### Phase 3: Metadata Options Model (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n  - Define package imports (dataclasses, typing)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Define `MetadataOptions` dataclass in `pack_models.py`\n  - Field `agent_name: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `language: Optional[str]` (default: \"python\")\n  - Field `entrypoint: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `port: Optional[int]` (default: 8080)\n  - Field `build_mode: Optional[str]` (default: \"local\")\n  - Field `requirements_file: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `description: Optional[str]` (default: None)\n  - Field `workload_manager_url: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `router_url: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `readiness_probe_path: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `readiness_probe_port: Optional[int]` (default: 8080)\n  - Field `registry_url: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `registry_username: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `registry_password: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n  - Field `agent_endpoint: Optional[str]` (default: \"\")\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\"` classmethod in `MetadataOptions`\n  - Create MetadataOptions from CLI options dict\n  - Handle missing keys with defaults\n\n### Phase 4: PackRuntime Implementation (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n  - Define package imports (logging, shutil, pathlib, typing)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Define `PackRuntime` class in `pack_runtime.py`\n  - Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n  - Initialize metadata_service\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Validate workspace structure\n  - Load or create metadata\n  - Apply CLI option overrides\n  - Validate language compatibility\n  - Process dependencies\n  - Generate Dockerfile\n  - Update pack metadata\n  - Prepare output path\n  - Return result dict with agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path, output_path\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `_validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Check workspace_path exists\n  - Check workspace_path is a directory\n  - Raise ValueError with descriptive message\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `_load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Try to load existing metadata\n  - Create default metadata if not found\n  - Return metadata\n\n- [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `_create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Infer language from options (default: python)\n  - Infer entrypoint using _infer_entrypoint\n  - Create AgentMetadata with defaults\n\n- [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `_apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Collect non-None, non-empty option values\n  - Update metadata dict\n  - Return new AgentMetadata instance\n\n- [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement `_validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Delegate to language-specific validation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-048**: Implement `_validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Check for .py files\n  - Raise ValueError if none found\n\n- [ ] **TASK-049**: Implement `_validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Check for pom.xml\n  - Raise ValueError if not found\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `_process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Delegate to language-specific dependency processing\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `_process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Log requirements.txt presence/absence\n  - (Future: validate requirements format)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `_process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path)` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Log pom.xml presence/absence\n  - (Future: validate pom.xml format)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `_generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Select language-specific generator\n  - Write Dockerfile to workspace\n  - Return dockerfile_path or None\n\n- [ ] **TASK-054**: Implement `_generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Generate FROM python:3.11-slim\n  - COPY requirements.txt and pip install\n  - COPY application code\n  - EXPOSE port\n  - ENTRYPOINT command\n\n- [ ] **TASK-055**: Implement `_generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Generate multi-stage build (maven builder + JRE runtime)\n  - COPY pom.xml and download dependencies\n  - Build with maven\n  - Copy jar to runtime image\n  - EXPOSE port\n  - ENTRYPOINT command\n\n- [ ] **TASK-056**: Implement `_update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path])` in `PackRuntime`\n  - Save metadata to agent_metadata.yaml\n\n- [ ] **TASK-057**: Implement `_prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path` in `PackRuntime`\n  - If output_path provided, copy workspace to output\n  - Create parent directories if needed\n  - Return output path or original workspace\n\n- [ ] **TASK-058**: Implement `_infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str` in `PackRuntime`\n  - For Python: look for main.py, app.py, or first .py file\n  - For Java: default to \"java -jar app.jar\"\n  - Return inferred entrypoint command\n\n### Phase 5: Runtime Stubs for Future Commands\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n  - Define `BuildRuntime` class with `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n  - Implement `build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` that raises NotImplementedError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Create `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n  - Define `PublishRuntime` class with `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")`\n  - Implement `publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` that raises NotImplementedError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n  - Define `InvokeRuntime` class with `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")`\n  - Implement `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None)` that raises NotImplementedError\n\n- [ ] **TASK-063**: Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n  - Define `StatusRuntime` class with `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")`\n  - Implement `get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]` that raises NotImplementedError\n\n### Phase 6: Service Stubs for Future Commands\n\n- [ ] **TASK-070**: Create `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n  - Define `DockerService` class with `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n  - Implement stubs: `check_docker_available`, `build_image`, `push_image`, `remove_image` (all raise NotImplementedError)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-071**: Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n  - Define `KubernetesProvider` class with `__init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)`\n  - Implement stub: `deploy_agent` (raises NotImplementedError)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-072**: Create `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n  - Define `AgentCubeProvider` class with `__init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None)`\n  - Implement stub: `deploy_agent_runtime` (raises NotImplementedError)\n\n### Phase 7: CLI Main Entry Point (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-080**: Create `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n  - Define package imports (json, logging, sys, pathlib, typing, typer, rich)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-081**: Initialize Typer app in `main.py`\n  - Create `app = typer.Typer()` with name, help, no_args_is_help, rich_markup_mode, add_completion=False\n\n- [ ] **TASK-082**: Implement `version_callback(value: bool)` in `main.py`\n  - Print version using rich console\n  - Raise typer.Exit()\n\n- [ ] **TASK-083**: Implement `main()` root callback in `main.py`\n  - Accept version and verbose options\n  - Configure logging if verbose\n\n- [ ] **TASK-084**: Implement `pack()` command in `main.py`\n  - Accept all pack options (workspace, agent_name, language, entrypoint, port, build_mode, description, output, verbose)\n  - Resolve workspace path\n  - Show progress spinner\n  - Call PackRuntime.pack\n  - Print success message with paths\n  - Handle errors with _handle_error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-085**: Implement `_handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool)` in `main.py`\n  - Print error message in red\n  - Print traceback if verbose\n  - Raise typer.Exit(1)\n\n### Phase 8: Example Agents\n\n- [ ] **TASK-090**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/main.py`\n  - Create simple Flask app with /health and /invoke endpoints\n  - Return JSON responses\n\n- [ ] **TASK-091**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/hello-agent/requirements.txt`\n  - Add flask dependency\n\n- [ ] **TASK-092**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/main.py`\n  - Create Flask app with /health and /invoke endpoints\n  - Implement basic math operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide)\n  - Return JSON responses\n\n- [ ] **TASK-093**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/math-agent/requirements.txt`\n  - Add flask dependency\n\n### Phase 9: Unit Tests\n\n#### PackRuntime Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Define pytest fixture `python_workspace` that creates temp directory with main.py and requirements.txt\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_pack_success` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Create PackRuntime\n  - Call pack with python_workspace\n  - Verify result contains agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path\n  - Verify files exist\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_missing_workspace` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Call pack with nonexistent path\n  - Verify ValueError raised with \"does not exist\" message\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_pack_validate_no_python_files` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Call pack with empty temp directory\n  - Verify ValueError raised with \"No Python files found\" message\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_pack_infer_entrypoint` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Pack workspace with main.py\n  - Load saved metadata\n  - Verify entrypoint is \"python main.py\"\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_pack_override_options` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Pack with custom agent_name, entrypoint, port, build_mode\n  - Verify metadata reflects overrides\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: Implement `TestPackRuntime.test_generate_python_dockerfile` in `test_pack_runtime.py`\n  - Pack Python workspace\n  - Read generated Dockerfile\n  - Verify contains FROM python:3.11-slim, EXPOSE, ENTRYPOINT\n\n#### MetadataService Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Define test imports (tempfile, pathlib, pytest, yaml)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_success` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Create agent_metadata.yaml with test data\n  - Load metadata\n  - Verify fields match\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_fallback` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Create agent.yaml (fallback filename)\n  - Verify metadata loads from fallback\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_load_metadata_not_found` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Call load_metadata with no metadata files\n  - Verify FileNotFoundError raised\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_save_metadata` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Create AgentMetadata\n  - Save to temp directory\n  - Verify file exists and content matches\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_validate_language` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Try to create AgentMetadata with invalid language\n  - Verify ValueError raised\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_validate_build_mode` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Try to create AgentMetadata with invalid build_mode\n  - Verify ValueError raised\n\n- [ ] **TEST-017**: Implement `TestMetadataService.test_validate_port_range` in `test_metadata_service.py`\n  - Try to create AgentMetadata with port=70000\n  - Verify ValueError raised\n\n### Phase 10: Test Fixtures\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/fixtures/__init__.py`\n  - Package marker\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/fixtures/valid_python_agent/main.py`\n  - Simple Python agent code\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/fixtures/valid_python_agent/requirements.txt`\n  - Test dependencies\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/fixtures/valid_java_agent/pom.xml`\n  - Basic Maven POM structure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-024**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/fixtures/valid_java_agent/src/main/java/App.java`\n  - Simple Java class\n\n- [ ] **TEST-025**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/__init__.py`\n  - Package marker\n\n- [ ] **TEST-026**: Create `cmd/cli/tests/conftest.py`\n  - Pytest configuration (asyncio_mode = \"auto\")\n  - Shared fixtures\n\n### Phase 11: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Create `cmd/cli/README.md`\n  - Package overview\n  - Installation instructions\n  - Quick start guide\n  - Usage examples\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add docstrings to all public classes and methods\n  - PackRuntime class and methods\n  - MetadataService class and methods\n  - AgentMetadata model\n  - MetadataOptions dataclass\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/README.md`\n  - Document example agents\n  - Include pack command examples\n\n### Phase 12: Build & Test Configuration\n\n- [ ] **BUILD-001**: Verify pyproject.toml pytest configuration\n  - Set testpaths = [\"tests\"]\n  - Set asyncio_mode = \"auto\"\n\n- [ ] **BUILD-002**: Verify pyproject.toml ruff configuration\n  - Set line-length = 100\n  - Set target-version = \"py310\"\n\n- [ ] **BUILD-003**: Verify pyproject.toml mypy configuration\n  - Set python_version = \"3.10\"\n  - Set strict = true\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version and exits\n- [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack` command accepts all specified options\n- [ ] Workspace validation works for Python (requires .py files) and Java (requires pom.xml)\n- [ ] Metadata loading falls back through filenames (agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml)\n- [ ] Metadata saves to agent_metadata.yaml in correct YAML format\n- [ ] CLI option overrides apply to metadata\n- [ ] Dockerfile generation works for Python agents\n- [ ] Dockerfile generation works for Java agents\n- [ ] Entrypoint inference works from workspace files\n- [ ] Verbose error handling shows traceback\n- [ ] Rich progress spinner displays during pack operation\n- [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n- [ ] Package installs via `pip install -e .`\n- [ ] Example agents pack successfully\n- [ ] Pydantic validators reject invalid language/build_mode/port values\n- [ ] All files have corresponding _test.go files (for .py files: _test.py pattern via test_*.py)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `typer[all]` | External (>=0.9.0) | CLI framework with Rich support |\n| `pydantic` | External (>=2.0.0) | Data validation with BaseModel |\n| `pyyaml` | External (>=6.0) | YAML parsing and dumping |\n| `httpx` | External (>=0.24.0) | HTTP client (future commands) |\n| `docker` | External (>=6.0.0) | Docker SDK (future commands) |\n| `rich` | External (>=13.0.0) | Terminal formatting |\n| `packaging` | External (>=23.0) | Version parsing |\n| `importlib-resources` | External (>=6.0.0) | Resource file access |\n| `semver` | External (>=3.0.0) | Semantic versioning |\n| `pytest` | External (>=7.4.0) | Testing framework |\n| `pytest-asyncio` | External (>=0.21.0) | Async test support |\n| `pytest-cov` | External (>=4.1.0) | Coverage reporting |\n| `pytest-mock` | External (>=3.11.0) | Mocking utilities |\n| `httpx-mock` | External (>=0.10.0) | HTTP mocking |\n| cli-toolkit/spec.md | Internal | CLI specification |\n| cli-toolkit/design.md | Internal | CLI design |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Internal | Python SDK design |\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-009 (Package structure)\n    ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-021 (Metadata models)\n    ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-032 (Metadata options)\n    ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-058 (PackRuntime)\n    ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-063 (Runtime stubs)\n    ↓\nTASK-070 → TASK-072 (Service stubs)\n    ↓\nTASK-080 → TASK-085 (CLI main)\n    ↓\nTASK-090 → TASK-093 (Example agents)\n    ↓\nTEST-001 → TEST-026 (Tests & fixtures)\n    ↓\nDOC-001 → DOC-003 (Documentation)\n    ↓\nBUILD-001 → BUILD-003 (Build config)\n```\n\n## Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing tests/`\n  - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify all .py files have corresponding test_*.py files\n  - Verify main logic paths covered\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml\n├── README.md\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── pack_models.py\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   ├── main.py\n│   │   └── requirements.txt\n│   └── math-agent/\n│       ├── main.py\n│       └── requirements.txt\n└── tests/\n    ├── __init__.py\n    ├── conftest.py\n    ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n    ├── test_metadata_service.py\n    └── fixtures/\n        ├── __init__.py\n        ├── valid_python_agent/\n        │   ├── main.py\n        │   └── requirements.txt\n        └── valid_java_agent/\n            ├── pom.xml\n            └── src/main/java/App.java\n```\n\n## Command Reference\n\n### pack Command\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n\nOptions:\n  -f, --workspace PATH          Path to agent workspace directory [default: .]\n  --agent-name TEXT             Override agent name\n  --language TEXT               Programming language (python, java)\n  --entrypoint TEXT             Override entrypoint command\n  --port INTEGER                Port to expose in Dockerfile\n  --build-mode TEXT             Build strategy: local or cloud\n  --description TEXT            Agent description\n  --output PATH                 Output path for packaged workspace\n  --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n  --help                        Show this message and exit\n```\n\n### Global Options\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]\n\nOptions:\n  --version                     Show version and exit\n  -v, --verbose                 Enable verbose output\n  --help                        Show this message and exit\n```\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```bash\n# Pack Python agent with defaults\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/agent\n\n# Pack with custom options\nkubectl-agentcube pack \\\n  --agent-name my-agent \\\n  --language python \\\n  --entrypoint \"python main.py\" \\\n  --port 8080 \\\n  --build-mode local \\\n  --output /tmp/packaged-agent\n\n# Pack with verbose output\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f ./my-agent --verbose\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **PackRuntime Tests**: Validate packaging logic, workspace validation, metadata handling\n2. **MetadataService Tests**: Validate metadata loading, saving, validation\n3. **Model Tests**: Validate Pydantic validators and dataclass behavior\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n- `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n- `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775865549411,"end":1775865549426}}}}
